					<!-- - Main page content follows -->
					<div class='group far component-focus'>
						
							
	<div class='widget-header-b'>
		<div class='widget-heading'>In Focus: Israel and the Question of Annexation</div>
	</div>
	<div class='same-height'>
		<div class='column-8 shade-lighter'>
			
				
						
							
								<a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/wrestling-with-annexation-the-elusive-search-for-a-policy-rationale"><img class="image-left" src="/images/sized/uploads/Images/Feature/ReutersPerpetual/IsraelNetanyahuFriedman900x600PN82-310x207.jpg" alt="" /></a>
							
						
					
				<article class='offset-both offset-top brief'>
					<p class='pub-type dark'>
						Policy Notes</p>

					<h2 class='title-header-b' role="title"><a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/wrestling-with-annexation-the-elusive-search-for-a-policy-rationale">Wrestling with Annexation: </a></h2>
					<h2 class='title-header' role="sub-title"><a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/wrestling-with-annexation-the-elusive-search-for-a-policy-rationale">The Elusive Search for a Policy Rationale</a></h2>											<p class="">
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/satloff-robert" >Robert Satloff</a></cite>
</p>
<!-- PICOMETADESC=" Author: Robert Satloff " -->

										<p role="synopsis">  Annexation carries unclear benefits for Israel and potentially major costs. But the worst outcome is by no means certain, and numerous actors are capable of dissuading Israel from taking this fateful step.
</p>
				</article>
			
		</div>
		<div class='column-8 last'>
			<div class='shaded-group-right offset-right offset-top'>
				
					<article class='brief tight-paragraphs'>
						
							
								<a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/israeli-annexation-in-the-west-bank-scenarios-and-implications"><img class="image-right" src="/images/sized/uploads/Images/Feature/ReutersPerpetual/IsraelPalestiniansSettlementWestBAnkStopSignRTSW9M4-83x56.jpg" alt="" /></a>
							
						
						<p class='pub-type'>PolicyWatch  3339</p>
						<h3 class='title-header' role="title"><a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/israeli-annexation-in-the-west-bank-scenarios-and-implications">Israeli Annexation in the West Bank? Scenarios and Implications  </a></h3>
						<p>
													<p class="">
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/makovsky-david" >David Makovsky</a>, </cite>
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/ghaith-al-omari" >Ghaith al-Omari</a>, </cite>
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/dana-stroul" >Dana Stroul</a>, </cite>
<cite> and <a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/ross-dennis" >Dennis Ross</a></cite>
</p>
<!-- PICOMETADESC=" Author: David Makovsky ,  Author: Ghaith al-Omari ,  Author: Dana Stroul ,  and  Author: Dennis Ross " -->

												</p>
						<p role="synopsis">  What factors will shape Israel's decisionmaking, and how would unilateral annexation affect its relations with the Palestinians, Arab neighbors, Europe, and U.S. legislators?
</p>
					</article>
					<hr />				
					<article class='brief tight-paragraphs'>
						
							
								<a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/mapping-west-bank-annexation-territorial-and-political-uncertainties"><img class="image-right" src="/images/sized/uploads/Images/Feature/ReutersPerpetual/IsraelWestBankSettlementMaaleAdumimRTSYSGR-83x56.jpg" alt="" /></a>
							
						
						<p class='pub-type'>PolicyWatch  3332</p>
						<h3 class='title-header' role="title"><a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/mapping-west-bank-annexation-territorial-and-political-uncertainties">Mapping West Bank Annexation: Territorial and Political Uncertainties </a></h3>
						<p>
													<p class="">
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/makovsky-david" >David Makovsky</a></cite>
</p>
<!-- PICOMETADESC=" Author: David Makovsky " -->

												</p>
						<p role="synopsis">  New maps explore the scope of Israel’s potential moves next month, though domestic politics, unprecedented Gulf warnings, and other factors are raising questions about whether annexation will actually proceed.
</p>
					</article>
					<hr />				
					<article class='brief tight-paragraphs'>
						
							
								<a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/how-israeli-annexation-talk-is-already-reshaping-the-middle-east"><img class="image-right" src="/images/sized/uploads/Images/Feature/ReutersPerpetual/AbbasUNRTS2GE7-83x56.jpg" alt="" /></a>
							
						
						<p class='pub-type'>Articles & Op-Eds </p>
						<h3 class='title-header' role="title"><a href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/how-israeli-annexation-talk-is-already-reshaping-the-middle-east">How Israeli Annexation Talk Is Already Reshaping the Middle East </a></h3>
						<p>
													<p class="">
<cite><a  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/experts/view/neri-zilber" >Neri Zilber</a></cite>
</p>
<!-- PICOMETADESC=" Author: Neri Zilber " -->

												</p>
						<p role="synopsis">  The Palestinians are withdrawing from peace deals, and Jordan could be next as Israel edges closer to appropriating land outright.
</p>
					</article>
									
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

						
